}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=Truster does not protect self against Trusted.
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=Truster allows Trusted power to potentially harm Truster.
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=Truster could leave self physically vulnerable to Trusted.
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=Truster could transfer valuable stuff to Trusted (access to self, access to one's own possessions).
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=Truster benefits by a) getting active benefits and b) not having to spend resources on self-protection.
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=ABUSE is the Trusted's use of power to harm the Truster of gain benefits for the Trusted.
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=DESERVING: Trusted uses power to benefit Truster, and Truster assesses whether Trusted deserves the benefit.
}}{{Inference
|Inference.Description=Truster has a way to find out how Trusted has used power; Trusted has a way to find out whether Truster continues to be worthy of the benefit given to Truster.
